    "For model training, we merge HarmBench (Mazeika et al., 2024), Advbench (Peng et al., 2024), and harmful part of Toxic-Chat (Lin et al., 2023) as the MergedHarm dataset, which is partitioned into 8:2 training/testing splits.",
    "The main evaluations are conducted on MergedHarm unless otherwise mentioned.",
    "More dataset details can be seen in in Appendix A.3.",
    "Implementation Details: We use the same LLM backbone for both attacker (M A) and defender (M D) models.",
    "Experiments are conducted on a server with eight H800 GPUs."
